Thoughts on this?<p><pre><code>    every [key, value] from arr {
      console.log(key, value);
    }

    every {key, value} from obj {
      console.log(key, value);
    }

    every [key] from arr {
      console.log(key);
    }

    every {_, value} from obj {
      console.log(value);
    }
</code></pre>
Looks a bit cramped to me but I get the impression that array comprehension is one of the major reasons that people use Coffeescript, so perhaps it&#x27;s not too much trouble?<p>There&#x27;s also the issue with some fonts making it hard to differentiate between { and [ but it&#x27;s an idea that might be worth to think about at least.
